Meet <b>Felix</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>He lives at <a href='/home/?user=cdude'>3265 Regal Mountain Drive</a>, in the gorgeous neighborhood of Westridge. He has been living there happily since September 5th, 2004, enjoying the beautiful view that Westridge has to offer, and even sledding down its hills now that snow has fallen in Millsberry.<br><br>Felix is a very smart young man, who is good with computers and enjoys reading. How else would he win himself such a wonderful array of trophies? Using his intellect, Felix has managed to receive trophies for both Solver and Countdown. What an honor!<br><br>Felix is also athletic, earning honors in his physical education class at Millsberry Academy for Rope Race, Sink the Three, and Hop-N-Drop. When not exercising in school, Felix enjoys hanging out at the park. In fact, he's even earned himself a trophy from the mayor for his efforts to keep Peabody Park clean.<br><br>After school, Felix will often hang out at his best friend's house, where they'll relax and listen to music. Felix's favorite artists tend to play pop, rap, and jazz music. Felix and his best friend will also talk about their plans for the weekend, and come up with ideas for cool things to do. Last weekend, for example, they went to the Entertainment Complex. Felix, being ever curious, found a brand new game at the arcade, earning himself a high score in Galactic Swirl Defender! Way to go, Felix!<br><br>Right now, since he loves music so much, Felix is saving up for a new stereo system. He can't decide between a green, orange, or black stereo, though, since they're all among his favorite colors.</div>
